{"guid": "MoJ 023", "title": "Prison Officer workforce", "measure_summary": "The data measures the number of full-time and part-time prison officers in England and Wales, broken down by ethnicity.\r\n\r\nIt includes prison officers in salary bands 3 to 5, which cover frontline prison officers and custodial managers. It is a \u2018snapshot\u2019 of the number of prison officers employed on 31 March each year.", "summary": "* in 2016, fewer than 6% of prison officers in England and Wales came from an ethnic minority background (excluding White ethnic minorities); this compares with 14% of people in England and Wales that belong to an ethnic minority group (excluding White ethnic minorities)\r\n* since 2013, Black and Other ethnic prison officers have seen the greatest reduction in their workforce, which have fallen by 44.2% and 43.2% respectively", "geographic_coverage": "England and Wales", "lowest_level_of_geography": "National", "time_covered": "2013 to 2016", "need_to_know": "Between 31 March 2013 and 31 March 2016, the total number of prison officers employed in England and Wales fell by more than a third, to 19,089. \r\n\r\nPrison officers give details of their ethnicity to an online administration system. However, they are not required to state their ethnicity, and many do not. In 2016, 16,448 stated their ethnicity\r\n\r\nThe percentages in the statistics presented here exclude prison officers whose ethnicities were not known. This adds a fairly high degree of uncertainty to the breakdowns by ethnicity.\r\n\r\nIf most of those prison officers not stating their ethnicity were in fact from an ethnic minority background, for example, the real percentage of ethnic minority prison officers would be higher than stated here. Conversely, if most prison officers who didn\u2019t state their ethnicity were White, the percentage of ethnic minority prison officers would be lower than the figure indicated in this measure.\r\n \r\nAs there\u2019s no way of knowing the ethnicity of those who didn\u2019t state theirs, the data isn\u2019t reliable enough to make a completely detailed or accurate assessment of the ethnic breakdown of the prison officer workforce.\r\n \r\nObservations on ethnicity based on this data should be treated with caution. This is because the percentage of prison officers who didn\u2019t state their ethnicity is considerably larger than the percentage of prison officers from an ethnic minority (not including White ethnic minorities).", "ethnicity_definition_summary": "Prison officers were asked to place themselves within the following 5 broad ethnic categories:\r\n\r\n* Asian/Asian British\r\n* Black/African/Caribbean/Black British\r\n* Chinese or Other ethnic group\r\n* Mixed/Multiple ethnic groups\r\n* White", "ethnicity_definition_detail": "", "source_text": "NOMS Annual Staff Equalities report", "source_url": "https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/noms-annual-staff-equalities-report-2015-to-2016", "department_source": "Ministry of Justice", "published_date": "", "last_update_date": "24/11/2016", "next_update_date": "November 2017", "frequency": "Annual", "related_publications": "", "contact_name": "Kate Shaw", "contact_phone": "020 3334 3536", "contact_email": "kate.shaw@noms.gsi.gov.uk", "data_source_purpose": "Administrative data used for internal management information", "methodology": "Data is derived from the staff administration system used by the National Offender Management Service. The numbers represent the data held at the point when extracts were taken. As with all large administrative data sources, some inherent inaccuracy may exist.", "data_type": "Administrative", "suppression_rules": "", "disclosure_control": "", "estimation": "", "type_of_statistic": "Official statistics", "qmi_url": "https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/638273/guide-workforce-statistics-30-june-2017.pdf", "further_technical_information": "[National Offender Management Service Staff Equalit